59
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,560
Noir!

60
00:03:56,550 --> 00:03:58,490
Hey!

61
00:03:59,130 --> 00:04:00,520
Morning!

62
00:04:00,980 --> 00:04:02,620
Morning, Emma.

63
00:04:02,620 --> 00:04:05,440
This is Emma Brightness.

64
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:08,750
She was born into a barony,
meaning her family is wealthy,

65
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:10,700
but our parents are friends,

66
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,600
and she's been my friend since we were kids.

67
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:15,580
We're both going to be
librarians starting today!

68
00:04:15,580 --> 00:04:17,110
Let us do our best!

69
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:20,990
Actually, about that, Emma...

70
00:04:20,990 --> 00:04:22,360
What?!

71
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:26,020
Th-Th-Then... you can't be a librarian?

72
00:04:26,450 --> 00:04:27,480
No...

73
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,490
But...

74
00:04:31,330 --> 00:04:33,490
Y-You're that disappointed?

75
00:04:33,490 --> 00:04:34,890
Well, I mean...

76
00:04:34,890 --> 00:04:37,610
I had some really good news!

77
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:40,090
About your skill.

78
00:04:40,090 --> 00:04:42,760
Skill? You mean my Great Sage skill?

79
00:04:43,130 --> 00:04:50,890
Skill [Great Sage]

80
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:46,320
The Great Sage skill
is my one and only skill.

81
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:50,890
Tells the user everything about the world
(even the unexplained).

82
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:49,270
It tells me everything about the world.

83
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:50,890
It's a pretty rare skill.

84
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:55,730
My parents jumped for joy when they
had my skill appraised at the church.

85
00:04:51,940 --> 00:04:53,580
Fantastic, my son!

86
00:04:53,580 --> 00:04:55,730
Oh, how wonderful!

87
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,560
But...

88
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:00,650
I can't use the Great Sage skill.

89
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:03,570
Q: What's tomorrow's
\h\h\h\hweather forecast?

90
00:05:01,690 --> 00:05:03,570
Well, actually, I can...

91
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:03,570
A: It'll be sunny!

92
00:05:03,850 --> 00:05:05,550
But every time I use it,

93
00:05:05,550 --> 00:05:08,960
I'm plagued with a headache
so bad that I wish for death.

94
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:11,260
Which is why I don't use it.

95
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:15,040
I just happened to be going through
the ancient texts yesterday,

96
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,820
and I found this passage...

97
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:22,200
"Whenever the great sage of old, Marlin,
was plagued with terrible headaches,

98
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:26,280
he demanded kisses from his wives."

99
00:05:26,670 --> 00:05:28,400
Why, though?

100
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:32,560
They must've been effective
against his headaches! Duh!

101
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,520
What?

102
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:36,140
Th-That makes sense, doesn't it?

103
00:05:37,150 --> 00:05:39,030
Actually, you might have a point.

104
00:05:41,010 --> 00:05:43,900
D-Do you want to give it a try?

105
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:45,240
Are you sure?

106
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:48,590
W-W-Well, who else are
you going to try that with?!

107
00:05:48,590 --> 00:05:51,630
It's just a kiss! And we've known
each other forever...

108
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:54,520
And we're totally adults!

109
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,610
In that case...

110
00:05:56,610 --> 00:05:57,410
Huh?!

111
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:02,870
W-Wait.

112
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:06,800
Let's find a better spot...

113
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,980
Y-You can go ahead.

114
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,150
I hope you're ready.

115
00:06:38,860 --> 00:06:39,960
You can do it!

116
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,900
Answer my query, Great Sage.

117
00:06:48,230 --> 00:06:49,330
As you wish.

118
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:53,580
I want to become stronger so I can pass
the exam for the Hero Academy.

119
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:55,890
What's the most efficient way
to become stronger?

120
00:06:56,310 --> 00:06:58,770
Explore a hidden dungeon.

121
00:06:58,770 --> 00:07:02,520
A hidden dungeon? Where's the closest one?

122
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:06,670
There lies a cave 15,000 meters
southwest of here.

123
00:07:06,670 --> 00:07:10,530
Activate the switch in the wall,
and you will find the Infinite Labyrin—

124
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,530
My head's killing me!

125
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:15,700
Should we kiss again?

126
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:16,830
Yes, please!

127
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:27,550
My headache's fading...

128
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:43,350
Does... your head still hurt?

129
00:07:43,350 --> 00:07:44,260
Yeah.

130
00:07:52,130 --> 00:07:53,610
I've got all the right gear.

131
00:07:54,410 --> 00:07:56,870
I even borrowed a sword from Father.

132
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:09,220
Is this where the switch is?

133
00:08:22,050 --> 00:08:25,140
You will need a spell to open the door.

134
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:27,230
And that spell is...

135
00:08:29,590 --> 00:08:32,060
"Hidden dungeon only I can enter!

136
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:34,570
Let me train in secret to become
the strongest in the world!"

137
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:52,300
This way.

138
00:09:12,630 --> 00:09:16,200
U-Um... You are alive, right?

139
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,490
Touch my head.

140
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:26,830
I am Olivia Servant!

141
00:09:24,370 --> 00:09:29,880
I am Olivia Servant
a totally super-awesome adventurer

142
00:09:26,830 --> 00:09:29,880
A totally super-awesome adventurer!

143
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:33,800
You see, I happened to stumble upon
this hidden dungeon on one of my walks.

144
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:36,590
I figured out how to get in all by myself.

145
00:09:36,590 --> 00:09:40,720
I ran into a monster on the second floor
and decimated it in two seconds.

146
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,720
Things were going peachy,

147
00:09:43,420 --> 00:09:45,600
but then a trap activated.

148
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,470
I've been tied up in here
for 200 years since then.

149
00:09:50,470 --> 00:09:52,800
For 200 years?! I'll undo your restraints right—

150
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:56,740
Nope, hold it. These are special
chains called Death Chains.

151
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:59,360
Cut them and say bye-bye to Olivia.

152
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:02,030
Huh? Then why did you call me here?

153
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:04,340
I've been looking for someone to talk to.

154
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:08,800
I figured no one would ever hear me,
but you actually showed up!

155
00:10:09,690 --> 00:10:14,030
You have no idea how long
I've been waiting for this moment!

156
00:10:14,590 --> 00:10:19,480
Anyway, you must have real potential,
considering you found this dungeon.

157
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,920
What's your name?

158
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,470
It's Noir Stardia.

159
00:10:22,470 --> 00:10:24,130
Noir, eh?

160
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:26,350
So what brought you here, anyway?

161
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:27,840
Well...

162
00:10:30,090 --> 00:10:32,940
Right. I got you.

163
00:10:33,770 --> 00:10:36,360
But I'm sure the Great Sage also said this!

164
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:40,520
"The super-hot babe Olivia
is sealed away in B2!"

165
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,870
Nope. He didn't say a word about you.

166
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:46,940
Well, whatever.
So you wanna get stronger, right?

167
00:10:46,940 --> 00:10:49,520
Then you can have my skills.

168
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:50,370
Huh?

169
00:10:50,370 --> 00:10:52,700
Well, I'm not going anywhere anytime soon...

170
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:55,760
So just tap your forehead against mine.

171
